Levels at eleven of the 14 dams within the Integrated Vaal River System have declined this week with the Vaal Dam hitting a three-year low. Courtesy #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Levels at 11 of the 14 dams within the Integrated Vaal River System have declined this week with the Vaal Dam hitting a three-year low. The Water and Sanitation Department is calling on customers to save as much water as possible. READ:Â Sisulu says schools will have enough water Sputnik Ratau speaks for the department, says this is to be expected because there been more consumption without any recharge of the dams. The Vaal Dam is currently at 45-percent capacity while last year in July it was at 67-percent.